  "prompt": "Is Rep. Ryan simultaneously campaigning for a house seat and the position of Vice President?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there is no publicly available information indicating that a U.S. Representative named Ryan is simultaneously campaigning for a House seat and the position of Vice President. Typically, candidates focus their efforts on a single office due to the significant logistical, financial, and strategic demands associated with campaigning. Running for two different offices at the same time can lead to conflicts of interest, divided attention, and potential legal complications, making it an uncommon practice in U.S. politics.\n\nIf you have a specific Representative Ryan in mind or if there have been recent developments after October 2023, I recommend checking the latest news sources or the official campaign websites for the most up-to-date and accurate information.",
